               <scopecontent id="aspace_520d28b4013d707c42dd4fd933527f28">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Contains paint, pencil, and ink drawings of pottery, motifs, and other creative designs. Depictions include Zuni pottery, Zuni blankets, Peruvian pottery, Navajo blankets, and other designs, objects, and patterns. Some drawings have annotations or identifiers added by Louise Everhardy.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c altrender="/repositories/11/archival_objects/3262137"
               id="aspace_6736cbce35c1b24ab0eaec6d24a80fbe"
               level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Artwork depicting cultural scenes</unittitle>
                  <physdesc/>
                  <physdesc localtype="container_summary">3 folders</physdesc>
                  <unitdate label="creation" unitdatetype="inclusive">undated</unitdate>
                  <container altrender="/repositories/11/top_containers/372246"
                             containerid="39002098814834"
                             encodinganalog="flat box (20d 1h 24w)"
                             id="aspace_6736cbce35c1b24ab0eaec6d24a80fbe_c1"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">6 (Oversize)</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_f52ad32b72cb43a2170d42a8d3cfe80e">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Contains pencil, crayon, and watercolor illustrations of cultural scenes including life in Zuni villages, hunting parties, wood chopping, food preparation, weaving, and other activities. Many drawings have annotations created by Louise Everhardy, including information about the artist.</p>
